FBIS4-51942 "dreas087__a94017" FBIS-EAS-94-087-A Daily Report 1 May 1994 ANNEX Japan SDPJ's Uehara Seeks `Grand Union of Doves' SDPJ's Uehara Seeks `Grand Union of Doves' OW0405044994 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 1 May 94 Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0405044994 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [Text] During talks with reporters in Naha city on 30 April, Kosuke Uehara disclosed that he would seek to establish a "grand union of doves" by gathering forces advocating protection of the Constitution from Sakigake [Harbinger], the Democratic Socialist Party, and a liberal group in the Liberal Democratic Party. Uehara is a member of the Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ], and former director general of the National Land Agency and Hokkaido and Okinawa Development Agency. On the formation of a "grand union of doves," Uehara said: "It will formulate its policies toward the Japan-U.S. security pact, Self-Defense Forces, and foreign affairs based on the agreement made when the coalition government was inaugurated."
